  abstract = {{$<$}jats:sec{$><$}jats:title{$>$}Purpose{$<$}/jats:title{$><$}jats:p{$>$}To design a lowcost, portable permanent magnetbased MRI system capable of obtaining in vivo MR images within a reasonable scan time.{$<$}/jats:p{$><$}/jats:sec{$><$}jats:sec{$><$}jats:title{$>$}Methods{$<$}/jats:title{$><$}jats:p{$>$}A discretized Halbach permanent magnet array with a clear bore diameter of 27 cm was designed for operation at 50 mT. Custombuilt gradient coils, RF coil, gradient amplifiers, and RF amplifier were integrated and tested on both phantoms and in vivo.{$<$}/jats:p{$><$}/jats:sec{$><$}jats:sec{$><$}jats:title{$>$}Results{$<$}/jats:title{$><$}jats:p{$>$}Phantom results showed that the gradient nonlinearity in the ydirection and zdirection was less than 5},
